The paper discusses the existence of scheduler side-channels in real-time systems, which is a security concern and falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on dynamic priority scheduling algorithms, which are commonly used in operating systems (cs.OS) and embedded systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a new algorithm, which involves analyzing task sets and scheduling algorithms, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and programming languages (cs.PL).
